It was not the 〈◊〉 , but the thing signified, viz. Christ crucified, to which Constantine shewed his affection, and by
whom he obtained all his victories;
〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 . by this God, not by this signe.

Let vs now see your proofes to the contrarie: the first whereof you frame thus;




All sinne is done and committed properly by the person in whom it is:

But this was not done by S. Paul. Ergo.
